Lesson - movement nutrition

---------- [L1]

Video link:                     https://youtu.be/8ao-1dTg6gE
Lesson audio link:              https://rss.com/podcasts/footnerdprogram/552599/

Creators: Tom Williams, James Dooner

Framework

"Movement Nutrition" phrase coined by Katy Bowman - 
Movement as Nutrition in our bodies
- defining mechanotransduction
- importance of load and inputs
- exercise vs movement
- frequent low level active rest all day long vs. 
- sedentary mover = someone who is seemingly active exercising everyday for an hour -even intensely- is considered to be sedentary
- Sedenatarism - definition and risk factors
- global sedentarism vs. local sedentarism
- movement nutrient profile 
- What does your movement diet look like?

Experiments (nano to macro)
What does your movement diet look like?
- How many hours do I spend sitting in a chair?
- How many hours a day do you spend moving?
- How many different types of exercise do you do?
- How is your musculoskeletal health? Take inventory of all the pains, tensions, stiffness and discomfort in all the areas of your body.
Get specific and precise


Audio lesson notes:
- detailed notes and timestamps from the audio lesson


